\date{2025-01-10}
\title{Independence of Discrete R.V.s}
\taxon{definition}

\p{
  Discrete r.v. #{X} and #{Y} are \strong{independent} if
  ##{
    F_{X, Y}(x, y) = F_X(x) F_Y(y)
  }
  and it is also equivalent to the condition:
  ##{
    P(Y = y \mid X = x) = P(Y = y)
  }
  for all #{y} and #{x} s.t. #{P(X = x) > 0}.
}